No fewer than 10 persons sustained serious injuries in a motor accident along the Osogbo/Gbongan expressway on Wednesday evening when a commercial bus collided with a car. Witnesses said the 18-seater commercial bus registration number EDE 593 XA swerved off the road and collided with an oncoming KIA saloon car with number plate KRD 832 EH Lagos State. There were 18 people in the commercial bus, while the car had two occupants. The Osun State Deputy Governor, Benedict Alabi, who was at the scene of the accident immediately it happened, directed that the injured persons should immediately be taken to the Ladoke Akintola University of Technology (LAUTECH) Teaching Hospital, Osogbo. Daily Trust learnt that the medical bills of the injured persons were settled on the account of the Deputy Governor, who led the state ambulance that conveyed them to the hospital. Alabi, who described the incident as “unfortunate and avoidable,” said the accident would have been prevented if traffic rules were strictly obeyed. Scores injured in ghastly Osogbo road crash 2 killed, 19 injured in head-on collision at Gada-Biyu 12 die, 6 injured in Kwara auto crash